Class MultiTreeMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.TreeMap<K,ArrayList<V>>
        • pr4.util.MultiTreeMap<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<K,ArrayList<V>>, NavigableMap<K,ArrayList<V>>, SortedMap<K,ArrayList<V>>

    public class MultiTreeMap<K,V>
extends TreeMap<K,ArrayList<V>>
    A TreeMap that supports multiple values for the same key, via ArrayLists. Values for the same key will be returned and traversed in order of insertion; that is, newer values with the same key will be stored after any other values with the same key.
